\begin_layout Standard
Random process is one of the most important object of mathematics.
 It is well described theoretically and has real life representations in
 almost every aspect of human life, from physics and biology to economy
 and social sciences.The random process itself is merely a series of realizations
 of random variables.
 Depending on the types of the random variables and their mutual interactions
 random processes can be splitted into a large nuber of different categories.
 Most common type of a discrete random process is a random walk, a mathematical
 object first introduced by K.Pearson in 1905 
